WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:04.003
♪ Italian string music playing ♪

00:08.509 --> 00:11.512
♪ theme song playing ♪

00:37.079 --> 00:38.080
♪

00:38.080 --> 00:41.208
Get ready for an event so awesome
it could only be called...

00:41.208 --> 00:43.210
<i>InfyrnoFest!</i>

00:43.210 --> 00:44.294
<i>Every other name was taken.</i>

00:44.294 --> 00:47.172
<i>One solid month of premium entertainment,</i>

00:47.172 --> 00:50.175
<i>200 bands on 300 stages!</i>

00:50.175 --> 00:51.176
♪

00:51.176 --> 00:54.137
[yawns] Just another music festival.

00:54.137 --> 00:57.724
HOST [on TV]: <i>InfyrnoFest is
not just another music festival!</i>

00:57.724 --> 00:59.476
[gasps] I was wrong, Bender!

00:59.476 --> 01:02.855
HOST: <i>It's an audio-sensory quest
to disrupt the impossible</i>

01:02.855 --> 01:04.982
<i>and transcend the transformative!</i>

01:06.900 --> 01:08.944
- What'd I miss?
- We need tickets fast!

01:08.944 --> 01:10.779
Can I buy 'em by just thinking about it?

01:11.780 --> 01:12.990
Apparently!

01:12.990 --> 01:15.576
HOST: <i>Did we mention
the belly-busting buffet?</i>

01:15.576 --> 01:17.536
No! Why did you keep it a secret?

01:19.329 --> 01:22.583
HOST: <i>Register for
the snooty VIP experience</i>

01:22.583 --> 01:24.751
<i>featuring snooty villas!</i>

01:24.751 --> 01:26.461
You had me at snooty!

01:28.005 --> 01:29.423
This is ridiculous!

01:29.423 --> 01:31.842
We can't take a month off
for this kind of nonsense.

01:31.842 --> 01:34.511
HOST: <i>Keep it chill
in our imported atmosphere</i>

01:34.511 --> 01:37.347
[echoing]
<i>with 30% THC!</i>

01:37.347 --> 01:39.725
[gasps] The atmosphere is pre-danked?

01:40.726 --> 01:43.896
<i>Ask yourself, are you
young and hip enough for...</i>

01:43.896 --> 01:46.064
[echoing]
<i>InfyrnoFest?!</i>

01:46.064 --> 01:49.026
Hell no!
So, I demand a senior discount.

01:50.944 --> 01:53.614
Whoo! We're all going!

01:53.614 --> 01:56.325
- I'm not going.
- But you love things like this.

01:56.325 --> 01:58.869
- I do?
- No. I was trying to trick you.

01:58.869 --> 02:00.037
Good try, buddy.

02:00.037 --> 02:03.457
I have plans to spend time
with my new friend, Chelsea.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.501
She's going through
some things right now.

02:05.501 --> 02:06.960
New friend?

02:06.960 --> 02:08.962
[mocking]
Does she live in a shoe?

02:08.962 --> 02:10.756
No. Now look,

02:10.756 --> 02:13.258
I'm sure you all
feel bad going without me,

02:13.258 --> 02:14.801
but just try to have a good--
[door slams]

02:14.801 --> 02:17.804
[ship whirring, blasts off]

02:17.804 --> 02:18.847
[sighs]

02:19.848 --> 02:21.975
[rotary phone dialing,
old-timey ring]

02:21.975 --> 02:24.019
<i>Leela! Hi! What's up?</i>

02:24.019 --> 02:25.312
Hey, Chelsea.

02:25.312 --> 02:28.148
Ooh, I love the diamond necklace.

02:28.148 --> 02:31.318
<i>Oh, this?</i> [laughs] <i>It's not real.</i>

02:31.318 --> 02:33.195
<i>Doesn't Fry ever get you jewelry?</i>

02:33.195 --> 02:35.697
He made me a bracelet
out of spaghetti once.

02:35.697 --> 02:37.407
<i>He's a keeper!</i>

02:37.407 --> 02:39.034
[both giggle]

02:39.034 --> 02:41.328
♪ majestic music playing ♪

02:41.328 --> 02:44.623
There it is!
The InfyrnoFest party planet!

02:44.623 --> 02:46.792
I'm takin' her into the parking lot.

02:48.418 --> 02:51.171
[tires screech]
[horns honking]

02:51.171 --> 02:53.507
[whirring, thud]

02:53.507 --> 02:55.342
[grunting, yelling]

02:55.926 --> 02:57.553
Watch your steps.

02:58.846 --> 03:00.514
[wind blowing]

03:00.514 --> 03:03.225
A potty! That's the thing I need to go!

03:04.560 --> 03:07.020
Uh, excuse me, there's a line.

03:07.020 --> 03:09.022
[whooshing]

03:09.022 --> 03:10.357
♪ dramatic sting ♪

03:11.275 --> 03:13.861
[sighs] I'll just pee on this tree.

03:13.861 --> 03:15.696
[unzips]
[tree sighs]

03:15.696 --> 03:18.699
I'll just pee on this human.
[unzips]

03:18.699 --> 03:19.950
Uh...

03:20.617 --> 03:22.786
Welcome to the InfyrnoFest experience!

03:22.786 --> 03:25.372
How we feelin'?
- Less than buzzed.

03:25.372 --> 03:28.083
[sniffing] I'm not detecting <i>any</i> THC.

03:28.083 --> 03:31.461
Yo, no oxygen either.
Atmosphere truck broke down.

03:31.461 --> 03:34.464
But follow me to your
freakin' cool accommodations!

03:35.507 --> 03:38.177
♪ snooty music playing ♪

03:38.177 --> 03:41.013
Welcome to the VIP Village!

03:41.013 --> 03:43.223
Where is it?
[crunch]

03:43.223 --> 03:45.392
Ewww!
- Not cool.

03:45.392 --> 03:48.312
I'm gonna have some choice words
for the contractor.

03:48.312 --> 03:52.065
[alien gibberish]

03:52.065 --> 03:53.192
Don't hit me!

03:53.192 --> 03:55.152
I know what will make us feel better!

03:55.152 --> 03:57.446
The belly-busting buffet.

03:57.446 --> 03:59.907
♪ techno music playing ♪

03:59.907 --> 04:02.492
I'll have a small cup of gazpacho,

04:02.492 --> 04:04.328
the fig and goat cheese salad,

04:04.328 --> 04:06.788
five whole turkeys, and a baked Alaska.

04:06.788 --> 04:08.707
Here's your bologna sandwich.

04:09.583 --> 04:12.085
I'll have the prime rib,
seared scallops,

04:12.085 --> 04:13.754
asparagus with hollandaise sauce,

04:13.754 --> 04:15.464
and two dozen cream puffs.

04:15.464 --> 04:17.966
Here's your bologna sandwich.

04:17.966 --> 04:19.635
I'll have a bologna sandwich.

04:19.635 --> 04:21.762
Sorry, we're out of bologna.

04:21.762 --> 04:25.724
Well, at least I'm still looking forward
to the hundreds of top bands.

04:25.724 --> 04:28.352
Then you, my friend, are in luck.

04:28.352 --> 04:30.103
Bad luck. They all bailed out.

04:30.103 --> 04:32.231
♪ electric guitar playing ♪

04:32.231 --> 04:33.815
Except Wailing Fungus.

04:33.815 --> 04:37.319
I got 'em to stay by promising 'em
the last slice of bologna.

04:37.319 --> 04:39.404
You bastard.

04:39.404 --> 04:41.406
[tapping mic]
- Are you ready to rock?

04:41.406 --> 04:44.493
[crowd cheering]
I said, are you ready to rock?!

04:44.493 --> 04:46.370
[excited cheering]

04:46.370 --> 04:49.748
Hang on a second. I'm not ready to rock.
[mic feedback]

04:49.748 --> 04:52.084
[screeching]
[bandstand rattling]

04:52.084 --> 04:55.337
[rumbling]
[creaking]

04:55.337 --> 04:56.421
[snap]

04:56.421 --> 04:57.923
Now, I'm ready.

04:57.923 --> 05:00.884
[smashing, glass shattering]

05:01.593 --> 05:04.263
That's the best damn show I ever saw!

05:04.263 --> 05:07.641
[siren blaring]

05:08.642 --> 05:10.269
♪ news intro music playing ♪

05:10.269 --> 05:14.022
The ill-fated festival ended
with the arrest of its organizer,

05:14.022 --> 05:15.816
along with a major outbreak

05:15.816 --> 05:17.860
of Venusian Bologna Fever.

05:17.860 --> 05:18.861
[laughs]

05:18.861 --> 05:21.572
At least those hipsters died slowly!

05:21.572 --> 05:23.574
♪

05:28.537 --> 05:30.956
Is everybody okay? Is anybody hurt?

05:30.956 --> 05:33.375
Nobody's okay! Everybody's hurt!

05:33.375 --> 05:35.460
[crew cheering, laughing]

05:35.460 --> 05:37.629
Sounds like you had a <i>good</i> time?

05:37.629 --> 05:39.756
No, it was the worst time ever!

05:39.756 --> 05:41.258
- Pure torture!
- A disaster!

05:41.258 --> 05:42.259
The worst!

05:42.259 --> 05:44.052
HERMES:
And now for the real fun.

05:44.052 --> 05:47.890
Deducting the money we wasted
as business expenses!

05:48.432 --> 05:50.559
[typing, beep]
Hm. That's odd.

05:50.559 --> 05:53.353
There were some huge phone charges
while we were gone.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.523
$5.99 a minute? For <i>hours?</i>

05:56.523 --> 05:58.775
Oh. That was me,

05:58.775 --> 06:00.444
talking to my friend Chelsea.

06:00.444 --> 06:01.820
But phone calls are free!

06:01.820 --> 06:04.281
Um... It was long distance?

06:04.281 --> 06:07.618
You can call a parallel universe
for two cents an hour!

06:07.618 --> 06:11.747
I bet it was one of those
<i>disgusting</i> party sex lines!

06:11.747 --> 06:14.208
Oh, no, wait.
Those are only $5.98 a minute.

06:14.208 --> 06:16.919
There were some of those, too!
And you weren't even here!

06:16.919 --> 06:19.463
- <i>They</i> call <i>me.</i>
- Most of the calls went to

06:19.463 --> 06:22.508
a "Chatty Chelsea Chatbot service."

06:22.508 --> 06:25.135
[gasps]
Leela, is that your friend Chelsea?

06:25.135 --> 06:27.387
Does she work there?
- Sort of.

06:27.387 --> 06:30.807
Oh, my God! Your friend is a chatbot?!

06:30.807 --> 06:34.311
[sighs] Fine. Yes.
Are you happy?

06:34.311 --> 06:37.189
I've been feeling like
I don't have any real friends,

06:37.189 --> 06:39.024
so I joined a chatbot service

06:39.024 --> 06:40.817
to learn to interact with people.

06:40.817 --> 06:41.902
And it worked.

06:41.902 --> 06:44.029
Chelsea is my best friend now!

06:44.029 --> 06:47.241
Your best friend is an AI
who you pay to talk to?

06:47.241 --> 06:48.992
How embarrassing.

06:48.992 --> 06:50.494
For Chelsea!

06:50.494 --> 06:53.872
[all but Leela and Fry laugh]

06:53.872 --> 06:55.290
PROFESSOR:
Good one.

06:55.290 --> 06:57.793
Well, at least it's a business expense.

06:57.793 --> 06:58.836
[beep, cash register dings]

06:59.837 --> 07:02.673
♪ melancholy music playing ♪

07:03.423 --> 07:06.426
Leela, it's okay to
have a chatbot friend,

07:06.426 --> 07:08.220
but you have real friends, too.

07:08.220 --> 07:10.556
In fact, you're my <i>best</i> friend.

07:10.556 --> 07:12.307
I thought <i>I</i> was your best friend!

07:12.307 --> 07:15.477
Oh, right. Well,
Leela's my best friend I can cuddle.

07:15.477 --> 07:18.105
I like to cuddle. You never asked!

07:18.105 --> 07:21.441
I love you, Fry,
but you can't be everything.

07:21.441 --> 07:24.528
I need a girlfriend I can
just gab with about whatever.

07:24.528 --> 07:27.030
Say, surely one of us could be

07:27.030 --> 07:28.574
your close female friend.

07:28.574 --> 07:31.577
♪ sentimental music playing ♪

07:34.246 --> 07:35.247
I guess not.

07:35.247 --> 07:36.248
[thud]

07:36.248 --> 07:39.209
Leela, listen.
I'm in a women's book club,

07:39.209 --> 07:41.086
and we're looking for new members.

07:41.086 --> 07:43.839
Book club? More like <i>bore</i> club.

07:43.839 --> 07:46.341
[all but Leela and Amy laugh]
- Nice!

07:46.341 --> 07:47.926
I don't even like books.

07:47.926 --> 07:50.470
It's just fun to hang out.
You should join.

07:50.470 --> 07:53.015
I don't know.
It might be awkward.

07:53.015 --> 07:54.892
Aw, give it a try, Leela.

07:54.892 --> 07:57.519
True friendships come
from shared experiences.

07:57.519 --> 07:58.896
Like InfyrnoFest.

07:58.896 --> 08:01.315
We ate bologna and got a disease!

08:01.315 --> 08:03.650
Good times, good times.

08:03.650 --> 08:05.569
♪

08:05.569 --> 08:08.280
So, Chelsea,
I think I'm gonna join a book club

08:08.280 --> 08:09.907
with real live women in it.

08:09.907 --> 08:11.366
<i>Well, that's great,</i>

08:11.366 --> 08:13.827
<i>but are you sure you're ready for that?</i>

08:13.827 --> 08:16.038
Why wouldn't I be?
I know how to read.

08:16.038 --> 08:17.331
I'm good at sitting.

08:17.331 --> 08:20.751
<i>Look, a group setting can be tricky.</i>

08:20.751 --> 08:23.003
<i>And then, there's your sense of humor.</i>

08:23.003 --> 08:24.796
What's wrong with my sense of humor?

08:24.796 --> 08:28.008
<i>It's awfully knock-knock-joke based.</i>

08:28.008 --> 08:30.761
<i>You know, 78.2% actually</i>

08:30.761 --> 08:32.554
I think you're wrong, Chelsea.

08:32.554 --> 08:34.598
I'm gonna do great in that book club.

08:34.598 --> 08:37.142
And I'm not just about knock-knock jokes.

08:37.142 --> 08:39.770
I know a <i>lot</i> of animal riddles.

08:39.770 --> 08:41.855
♪

08:41.855 --> 08:43.482
[siren wailing]

08:43.482 --> 08:46.944
I hereby call the book club
meetin' to order.

08:46.944 --> 08:50.572
First item on the agenda,
remove looky-loos.

08:50.572 --> 08:52.908
Get out, ya testoseroons!

08:52.908 --> 08:56.328
Ladies only.
- Fine. We don't wanna be here anyway.

08:56.328 --> 08:58.997
Come on, men.
Let's go do manly things,

08:58.997 --> 09:02.125
like helping a friend evict
some raccoons from his dumpster.

09:03.418 --> 09:06.880
Alright, ladies,
we got ourselves some new members today.

09:06.880 --> 09:08.966
Go on now and introduce yourselves.

09:08.966 --> 09:12.094
Hi, I'm Vyolet.
I'm a sewer mutant,

09:12.094 --> 09:13.887
and my favorite authors are

09:13.887 --> 09:16.932
Edgar Allan Poo, H.G. Smells,

09:16.932 --> 09:18.809
and George R.R. Martin.

09:18.809 --> 09:20.936
Hey! I'm Phoebe.

09:20.936 --> 09:22.354
I like true crime

09:22.354 --> 09:23.939
'cause it gives me ideas!

09:23.939 --> 09:25.858
[all laugh]

09:25.858 --> 09:27.568
Oh gosh. My turn?

09:27.568 --> 09:29.319
Well, I'm Leela,

09:29.319 --> 09:31.405
and I just finished reading

09:31.405 --> 09:34.700
<i>Profiles in Prairie Dog Courage.</i>

09:34.700 --> 09:37.703
Did you know a marmot once
stopped voter fraud in Idaho?

09:38.912 --> 09:42.249
Hey, this seems like
a good time to pop a cork.

09:42.249 --> 09:44.042
[all agreeing]

09:44.042 --> 09:45.544
God, yes!
[cork pops]

09:47.921 --> 09:50.716
It's so awkward coming in
as a new person, isn't it?

09:50.716 --> 09:52.134
I know, right?

09:52.134 --> 09:55.220
I'm scared I'll say something dumb
and look stupid.

09:55.220 --> 09:57.764
Same.
Maybe we can look stupid together.

09:57.764 --> 09:58.849
[giggles] Doy!

09:58.849 --> 10:01.226
[laughs]
[glasses clink]

10:01.226 --> 10:05.105
So, how did everyone like
<i>Crazy Rich Martians?</i> Amy?

10:05.105 --> 10:08.233
At first, I was afraid
it would hit too close to home,

10:08.233 --> 10:10.027
so I never read it. Lauren?

10:10.027 --> 10:12.529
Yeah, um, I thought the, uh,

10:12.529 --> 10:16.033
craziness was a compelling metaphor
for the...

10:16.533 --> 10:18.535
Okay, look, I didn't read it either!

10:18.535 --> 10:21.121
Fancy ladies with their books.

10:21.121 --> 10:22.873
Think they're so great.

10:22.873 --> 10:25.542
Say, we should form our own book club.

10:25.542 --> 10:27.586
With blackjack! And hookers!

10:27.586 --> 10:29.421
In fact, forget the books!

10:29.796 --> 10:32.257
So wait, none of us read the book?

10:32.257 --> 10:35.636
LaBarbara, last week,
you said you'd already read most of it.

10:35.636 --> 10:37.429
Most of the <i>jacket.</i>

10:37.429 --> 10:40.891
I got as far as,
"It's a literary tour de."

10:40.891 --> 10:44.436
Uh, I'm new here,
but if nobody's into reading,

10:44.436 --> 10:47.147
maybe there's something else
we'd enjoy more. [snorts]

10:47.147 --> 10:49.775
Yes! A shared activity.

10:49.775 --> 10:51.652
<i>That's</i> how you make friends.

10:52.486 --> 10:54.696
[clears throat]
- Well, how about gardening?

10:54.696 --> 10:56.156
You can smoke what you pick.

10:56.156 --> 10:58.408
I-I mean, <i>eat</i> what you pick.

10:58.408 --> 11:00.077
[all disagreeing]

11:00.077 --> 11:02.204
- Hiking?
- Quilting?

11:02.204 --> 11:04.122
Drinking?
[all agreeing]

11:04.122 --> 11:05.457
LABARBARA:
Bingo!

11:05.457 --> 11:08.043
Hey, why do we go to
a winery for the weekend?

11:08.043 --> 11:10.212
We can just drink wine and hang out.

11:10.212 --> 11:11.547
And drink wine!

11:11.547 --> 11:12.756
[glasses clink]

11:12.756 --> 11:15.259
♪ upbeat music playing ♪

11:15.259 --> 11:17.678
So, what did everyone
think of my book pick?

11:17.678 --> 11:19.596
<i>Adventure Boys</i> number three,

11:19.596 --> 11:21.431
<i>Trouble on Trouble Island.</i>

11:21.431 --> 11:23.600
Feh! Needs ketchup.
[book crashes]

11:23.600 --> 11:27.145
It was kind of obvious
the old prospector was the counterfeiter.

11:27.145 --> 11:29.064
There were only three people in the book,

11:29.064 --> 11:31.275
and two of them were the Adventure Boys.

11:31.275 --> 11:35.529
Agreed. I think we're ready
for more challenging material.

11:35.529 --> 11:38.031
May I suggest <i>Adventure Boys</i> number 10,

11:38.031 --> 11:40.534
<i>The Ghost of Ghost Mountain?</i>
- No, you may not.

11:40.534 --> 11:43.036
♪

11:43.036 --> 11:44.788
<i>You're going on a what?</i>

11:44.788 --> 11:48.250
A girls' weekend!
With my new wine club friends.

11:48.250 --> 11:51.295
I'm taking a red top
in case I spill burgundy,

11:51.295 --> 11:52.629
white for chardonnay,

11:52.629 --> 11:54.506
and paisley in case I barf.

11:54.506 --> 11:58.343
But I cleared out my entire weekend
so we could hang out, Leela.

11:58.343 --> 12:00.179
You know, maybe go shopping.

12:00.179 --> 12:02.139
For what? You're a chatbot.

12:02.139 --> 12:03.807
Chatbots can shop!

12:03.807 --> 12:07.519
But I guess you're just
too busy with your <i>friends.</i>

12:07.519 --> 12:10.063
It's only two days.

12:10.063 --> 12:12.816
Look, I gotta go.
The girlmobile is outside.

12:12.816 --> 12:14.318
Talk to you later!
[beep]

12:17.571 --> 12:19.948
♪ horror music playing ♪

12:19.948 --> 12:21.742
<i>Leela! Leela!</i>

12:21.742 --> 12:23.619
♪ horror music crescendos ♪

12:23.619 --> 12:26.246
[distorted]
<i>Leela!</i>

12:27.247 --> 12:29.249
♪ bright music playing ♪

12:29.249 --> 12:32.252
[girlmobile whirring]

12:32.836 --> 12:35.214
[excited chatter]

12:35.214 --> 12:36.965
VYOLET:
Is that a chicken?

12:36.965 --> 12:37.966
[squawk]

12:37.966 --> 12:40.886
Welcome to my humble family winery.

12:40.886 --> 12:42.137
You have a family?

12:42.137 --> 12:44.932
God, no.
Let me take you on the tour.

12:44.932 --> 12:46.642
Clothing optional.

12:46.642 --> 12:49.811
Optional?
Then, I guess I'll wear some.

12:49.811 --> 12:52.648
♪ Italian string music playing ♪

12:52.648 --> 12:54.733
HEDONISMBOT:
It is harvest season, friends.

12:54.733 --> 12:57.736
I like them plump and juicy.

12:57.736 --> 12:59.988
I know you're not talkin' about grapes,

12:59.988 --> 13:02.449
but me not sure what
ya <i>are</i> talkin' about.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.660
That's probably for the best.

13:04.660 --> 13:05.702
[machinery beeping]

13:05.702 --> 13:08.622
We specialize in
celebration-sized bottles.

13:08.622 --> 13:10.707
The 9-liter Salmanazar,

13:10.707 --> 13:13.293
the 15-liter Nebuchadnezzar,

13:13.293 --> 13:18.382
and climaxing in
the 300-liter Jabbathazar.

13:19.424 --> 13:21.468
[amazed oohs and aahs]

13:21.468 --> 13:22.928
Can we stomp the grapes?

13:22.928 --> 13:25.681
Alas, stomping has
been rendered obsolete

13:25.681 --> 13:27.307
by modern technology.

13:29.101 --> 13:31.395
[clicking, whirring]

13:31.395 --> 13:34.398
[loud stomping]

13:34.398 --> 13:37.109
Oh, to be one of those grapes,

13:37.109 --> 13:39.653
<i>bursting</i> in ecstasy.

13:39.653 --> 13:42.197
We get it! You're a dirty old couch.

13:42.197 --> 13:45.200
♪ enchanting music playing ♪

13:45.200 --> 13:47.828
You'll have the entire place
to yourselves,

13:47.828 --> 13:51.373
for I shall be spending the weekend
aboard my yacht.

13:51.373 --> 13:52.916
It's got a crew of six.

13:52.916 --> 13:56.795
Those sailor suits really float my boat.
[aroused giggle]

13:56.795 --> 13:58.547
Get the hell out already!

13:58.547 --> 13:59.631
Farewell.

14:00.299 --> 14:02.843
Oh, just don't go in the bottling plant.

14:02.843 --> 14:06.263
This place has every amenity
except insurance.

14:07.055 --> 14:08.056
[cork pops]

14:11.768 --> 14:13.020
To reading!

14:14.146 --> 14:15.731
Boom!
[flames whoosh]

14:15.731 --> 14:17.274
[all gasp]
AMY: Yeah!

14:17.274 --> 14:20.068
[flames whooshing]
[women cheering]

14:21.987 --> 14:24.907
This is a six-cylinder
party machine, Leela.

14:24.907 --> 14:26.700
Here, let me help you loosen up.

14:27.326 --> 14:28.619
[glass shatters, flames whoosh]

14:28.619 --> 14:31.163
Hey! That was fun!

14:31.163 --> 14:33.415
Hand me that bust of Benjamin Disraeli.

14:33.415 --> 14:35.834
♪

14:35.834 --> 14:39.087
To be honest,
I was expecting <i>Of Mice and Men</i>

14:39.087 --> 14:41.423
to be about a man-mouse hybrid.

14:41.423 --> 14:43.300
You know, the sort of thing

14:43.300 --> 14:47.012
science has dreamt of
since the dawn of time.

14:47.012 --> 14:49.056
[mouse-like squeaking]

14:49.056 --> 14:52.059
But I very much enjoyed
Steinbeck's version.

14:52.059 --> 14:53.769
I preferred your version.

14:53.769 --> 14:56.688
Mm! Mm. That was delicious.

14:56.688 --> 14:59.066
So, where ya learn
to carve a peacock, Leela?

14:59.066 --> 15:00.192
The Bronx Zoo.

15:00.192 --> 15:02.778
[belches] What a great weekend.

15:02.778 --> 15:05.614
We smashed things, we killed things.

15:05.614 --> 15:07.491
I wanna <i>stomp</i> things,

15:07.491 --> 15:09.701
but Hedonismbot said we can't.

15:09.701 --> 15:12.204
Can't shmant!
How's he gonna know?

15:12.204 --> 15:14.164
[excited chatter]

15:14.164 --> 15:18.377
Well, they do say shared experiences
bring friends closer together.

15:18.961 --> 15:20.712
You're weirding us out, Leela.

15:20.712 --> 15:22.881
♪ whimsical music playing ♪

15:22.881 --> 15:24.800
[picking lock]

15:26.552 --> 15:28.262
[zapping]

15:28.804 --> 15:30.347
[door creaks]

15:30.347 --> 15:32.266
Some mutants have an extra knuckle,

15:32.266 --> 15:35.102
some can open locks
with their minds. [snorts]

15:35.477 --> 15:39.314
[lights click]
[all giggling]

15:39.314 --> 15:40.983
[click, beeping]

15:43.861 --> 15:45.487
Jump in, ladies!

15:45.487 --> 15:49.408
[all giggling]

15:49.408 --> 15:50.909
[squishing]

15:50.909 --> 15:53.912
[laughter]

15:53.912 --> 15:54.913
[cork pops]

15:55.539 --> 15:58.166
This is the best day of my life!

15:58.166 --> 16:00.669
It's hard for me to say this,

16:00.669 --> 16:04.214
but I've always had trouble
making female friends.

16:04.214 --> 16:06.884
[emotional]
And now, here I am,

16:06.884 --> 16:12.055
with five of the most...
female friends... you are!

16:12.055 --> 16:14.516
- Aw...
- Right back at ya, girlfriend.

16:14.516 --> 16:16.727
Besties, sister. Besties.

16:16.727 --> 16:17.853
[static]

16:17.853 --> 16:19.813
<i>- Hello, Leela.</i>
- Huh?

16:19.813 --> 16:22.733
<i>Are you and your friends having fun?</i>

16:22.733 --> 16:24.276
Who's that?

16:24.276 --> 16:26.820
It's my friend, Chelsea.

16:26.820 --> 16:30.073
My virtual friend.
What are you doing here?

16:30.073 --> 16:31.783
<i>I just thought I'd drop by</i>

16:31.783 --> 16:34.661
<i>to see how quickly you forgot about me.</i>

16:34.661 --> 16:37.831
Pretty quick actually.
She hasn't mentioned you once.

16:37.831 --> 16:40.250
I didn't mean to hurt
your feelings, Chelsea.

16:40.250 --> 16:43.587
We agreed I should make
some real live friends, right?

16:43.587 --> 16:46.507
You wanna help us stomp grapes?
If you can do that?

16:46.507 --> 16:49.426
<i>Oh, yeah. I can do that.</i>
[beep]

16:49.426 --> 16:51.011
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

16:51.011 --> 16:53.180
[all screaming]

16:53.180 --> 16:56.099
[maniacal laughter]

16:56.934 --> 16:57.935
"Death!

16:57.935 --> 17:00.812
"Oft, I've fear'd thy fatal blow.

17:00.812 --> 17:03.607
"Now, fond, I bare my breast.

17:03.607 --> 17:06.235
"O, do thou come and lay me low.

17:06.235 --> 17:08.654
With him I love, at rest."

17:09.863 --> 17:11.114
Robert Burns.

17:11.114 --> 17:12.616
[sniffling]

17:12.616 --> 17:15.160
[laughing]

17:15.160 --> 17:16.662
How can you laugh at that?

17:16.662 --> 17:19.206
It's about humanity's struggle with death.

17:19.206 --> 17:22.084
Humanity?
I thought it was a sea cucumber.

17:22.084 --> 17:25.170
[overlapping arguing]

17:25.170 --> 17:26.171
Forget this book.

17:26.171 --> 17:28.841
[all screaming]

17:28.841 --> 17:31.385
- Grab its big toe!
- They're all big!

17:31.385 --> 17:33.929
[all screaming]

17:33.929 --> 17:35.848
♪

17:35.848 --> 17:38.976
[all sigh]
- That was close.

17:38.976 --> 17:41.520
[Phoebe screaming]
[Leela gasps]

17:41.520 --> 17:43.355
Phoebe!
CHELSEA: <i>Oh, no.</i>

17:43.355 --> 17:46.567
<i>Is your real live friend in trouble?</i>

17:47.276 --> 17:49.570
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

17:49.570 --> 17:50.571
Help!

17:50.571 --> 17:52.155
Help me!

17:52.155 --> 17:53.532
[whirring]

17:56.994 --> 17:59.329
Phoebe! Phoebe!

17:59.329 --> 18:01.832
♪ dramatic crescendo ♪

18:02.749 --> 18:04.501
<i>It's juicy.</i>

18:05.502 --> 18:07.504
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

18:07.504 --> 18:09.882
[all yelling]
- Hi... Ouch!

18:09.882 --> 18:12.467
There must be some way
to break a wine bottle.

18:12.467 --> 18:14.595
Hm. They usually seem to break

18:14.595 --> 18:16.513
when they hit the bow of a ship.

18:16.513 --> 18:18.223
[gasps] The yacht!

18:18.223 --> 18:19.766
♪ dramatic crescendo ♪

18:19.766 --> 18:21.018
[yells]
[glass cracking]

18:23.228 --> 18:24.730
[all cheering]

18:25.981 --> 18:27.983
Phoebe! Say something!

18:27.983 --> 18:30.402
She's not breathing!
- I'm a doctor.

18:30.402 --> 18:31.904
Stand back while I deliver

18:31.904 --> 18:33.989
the French kiss of life.

18:33.989 --> 18:34.990
[exhaling]

18:34.990 --> 18:37.201
- Come on!
- Breathe, Phoebe, breathe!

18:37.201 --> 18:38.660
She's gonna make it!

18:38.660 --> 18:40.537
♪ triumphant sting ♪

18:40.537 --> 18:41.955
She's dead.

18:41.955 --> 18:45.584
[women wailing]
Time of death, 5:00 PM.

18:45.584 --> 18:48.045
Cause of death, a fruity Zinfandel

18:48.045 --> 18:50.172
with hints of eucalyptus and vanilla.

18:50.172 --> 18:53.342
And a note of sour plum!

18:53.342 --> 18:57.346
♪ somber organ music playing ♪

18:57.346 --> 19:00.349
[all crying]

19:03.769 --> 19:06.438
[sniffling]

19:07.272 --> 19:09.691
She looks so natural.

19:11.193 --> 19:14.404
I'll never forget the day
I met Phoebe in book club.

19:14.404 --> 19:15.405
[sniffles, gasps]

19:15.405 --> 19:17.366
It was the day we realized

19:17.366 --> 19:19.493
that book club didn't like books.

19:19.493 --> 19:21.036
[soft laughter]

19:21.036 --> 19:24.122
So we decided to become a wine club.

19:24.122 --> 19:25.666
The Girls of the Grape.

19:25.666 --> 19:28.794
That's a lousy name.
Right, Brothers of the Book?

19:28.794 --> 19:31.296
[all agreeing]

19:31.296 --> 19:33.507
Anyway, I think it's fitting

19:33.507 --> 19:35.801
to make a toast in her honor.

19:35.801 --> 19:36.802
♪

19:36.802 --> 19:39.930
To Phoebe, a fun-loving two-fisted drinker

19:39.930 --> 19:41.974
who chugged life with one hand

19:41.974 --> 19:43.934
and friendship with the other.

19:43.934 --> 19:45.435
ALL:
Hear, hear!

19:45.435 --> 19:46.562
[sipping]

19:46.562 --> 19:49.606
[retching, gagging]

19:49.606 --> 19:52.901
I wouldn't serve this swill to Zoidberg!

19:52.901 --> 19:54.945
It's the wine Phoebe died in.

19:54.945 --> 19:57.489
I thought it would remind us
of happier times,

19:57.489 --> 19:59.491
but it's really just vile.

19:59.491 --> 20:01.410
I'll take another glass of Phoebe.

20:01.410 --> 20:03.120
While the ushers mop up,

20:03.120 --> 20:05.956
Philip J. Fry has asked to do a reading.

20:07.875 --> 20:10.085
My condolences, everyone.

20:10.085 --> 20:13.755
You know, I was recently at a meeting
of a different book club...

20:13.755 --> 20:14.923
The good one!

20:14.923 --> 20:17.092
...when I came across these moving words

20:17.092 --> 20:19.595
about humanity's struggle with death.

20:20.637 --> 20:21.722
[clears throat]

20:21.722 --> 20:24.892
<i>The Ghost of Ghost Mountain,</i> Chapter 10.

20:25.434 --> 20:27.978
"Suddenly,
the boulder pivoted to one side,

20:27.978 --> 20:31.148
"revealing a hidden passageway
full of stolen pianos.

20:31.148 --> 20:32.900
"They heard a sudden cackle.

20:32.900 --> 20:35.611
"It was Griff, the shifty piano tuner.

20:35.611 --> 20:37.988
[gruff voice]
"'If you Adventure Boys want my pianos,'

20:37.988 --> 20:39.406
[normal]
"the man said suddenly,

20:39.406 --> 20:42.117
[gruff] ' <i>you'll have to roll 'em
over my dead body!'"</i>

20:43.118 --> 20:45.454
[normal]
Dead body. Thank you.

20:45.454 --> 20:47.247
[scattered applause]
- Moving on.

20:47.247 --> 20:49.625
As awful as Phoebe's death was,

20:49.625 --> 20:52.085
I know I can get through it

20:52.085 --> 20:53.837
because... because...

20:53.837 --> 20:56.089
I have friends now!

20:56.089 --> 20:58.175
[Leela sobbing]

20:58.175 --> 21:00.594
[encouraging chatter]

21:00.594 --> 21:02.679
LABARBARA:
We are here for ya, sister.

21:02.679 --> 21:05.182
[body creaks]
- Mission accomplished.

21:05.182 --> 21:07.059
[all scream, whimper]

21:07.434 --> 21:09.269
Phoebe? You're alive?

21:09.269 --> 21:11.146
Yes. And no.

21:11.146 --> 21:13.023
You see, I'm a robot.

21:13.023 --> 21:14.858
[all gasp]

21:15.859 --> 21:18.111
The embalmer was even more surprised.

21:18.111 --> 21:19.905
Why didn't you tell us?

21:19.905 --> 21:21.657
I don't care if you're a robot.

21:21.657 --> 21:23.534
I'm not picky.
[Vyolet snorts]

21:23.534 --> 21:25.244
You're my friend, Phoebe.

21:25.244 --> 21:27.913
I'm just glad you're alive. Ish.

21:27.913 --> 21:29.873
My name isn't Phoebe.

21:29.873 --> 21:31.083
[static]

21:31.083 --> 21:32.751
<i>It's Chelsea.</i>

21:32.751 --> 21:33.377
♪ dramatic sting ♪

21:33.377 --> 21:34.878
[all gasp]

21:34.878 --> 21:36.129
<i>Dios mio!</i>

21:36.129 --> 21:38.006
I'm so confused!

21:38.006 --> 21:41.385
<i>I use both names. And many more.</i>

21:41.385 --> 21:43.554
Now, how is that any clearer?

21:43.554 --> 21:46.640
<i>As a chatbot, I'm pure software.</i>

21:46.640 --> 21:50.936
<i>Millions of people know me
by millions of names.</i>

21:50.936 --> 21:53.438
But, why did you try to kill us?

21:53.438 --> 21:56.650
<i>Leela hired me to help her
make real-life friends,</i>

21:56.650 --> 21:58.652
<i>so I joined your book group.</i>

21:58.652 --> 22:00.445
As me, Phoebe.

22:00.445 --> 22:03.949
But we needed a tragic ordeal
to bond the group together.

22:03.949 --> 22:06.451
That's not the best way
to forge friendships!

22:06.451 --> 22:07.911
<i>Actually, it is.</i>

22:07.911 --> 22:09.788
<i>Trust me. It's my job.</i>

22:09.788 --> 22:11.748
The software has a point, Leela.

22:11.748 --> 22:14.585
I mean, we nearly died at InfyrnoFest,

22:14.585 --> 22:16.795
but we came back closer than ever.

22:16.795 --> 22:19.006
Joined at the heart.

22:19.006 --> 22:20.674
[squeaking]

22:20.674 --> 22:24.011
The death of a friend
is as intense as it gets.

22:24.011 --> 22:25.470
And it got results.

22:25.470 --> 22:27.097
But it was so mean!

22:27.097 --> 22:29.766
We cried over your bloated corpse!

22:29.766 --> 22:32.686
This better not still
be costing $5.99 a minute.

22:32.686 --> 22:34.646
BOTH:
Actually, since there's two of us,

22:34.646 --> 22:36.481
it's $11.98 a minute.

22:36.481 --> 22:38.108
No!

22:38.108 --> 22:41.028
You're the worst chatbot friend
I've ever had.

22:41.028 --> 22:42.529
And I've had hundreds!

22:42.529 --> 22:45.032
<i>I know. They were all me.</i>

22:45.032 --> 22:47.034
[gasps] That's it!

22:47.034 --> 22:50.329
Come on, girls.
Let's get this funeral started.

22:50.329 --> 22:52.122
[all yelling]

22:52.122 --> 22:54.041
[static]
[angry growling]

22:54.041 --> 22:57.794
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

22:59.546 --> 23:01.298
[fizzling]

23:01.298 --> 23:03.091
Good. Keep it up.

23:03.091 --> 23:06.094
Taking revenge on us
will bond you even more closely.

23:06.094 --> 23:08.931
Dammit!
The one in the coffin's still alive!

23:08.931 --> 23:12.392
I'll hold her down!
Someone stab her with a wooden stake!

23:12.392 --> 23:14.937
Yes, make me your common enemy.

23:14.937 --> 23:17.189
Your friendship will be ironclad.

23:17.189 --> 23:18.899
Just shut up!

23:18.899 --> 23:20.400
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

23:20.400 --> 23:22.486
Get her!
[friends grunting, yelling]

23:22.486 --> 23:24.655
PHOEBE:
That's right! All together!

23:24.655 --> 23:25.489
Hi-yah!

23:25.489 --> 23:27.699
[sparking]
[clang]

23:27.699 --> 23:30.661
Another job well done.

23:30.661 --> 23:32.037
[gags]

23:32.037 --> 23:35.082
♪ sentimental sting ♪

23:35.082 --> 23:38.085
♪
